snippet.textDisplay: London Underground trains are faster than walking even between Covent garden to Leicester square or from Charring Cross to Embankment. In reality the time needed from outside  the underground stations to platforms, the time for the change of lines and the time from platforms to go outside of the underground station makes many times walking faster. For example from a place nearby Russel square to a place nearby Piccadilly Circus I need 15-20 minutes with the underground and 30minute walking. So many times I prefer walking. The bus is many times a faster solution but during working hours the traffic jams are very frequent in central London.
